{"title": "Modern life and memory lapses: It\u2019s okay to forget", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2023-11-12", "content": "The other night, I stopped my car at a traffic junction near my home. When the light turned green, I froze for a couple of seconds, unsure whether to drive straight or turn right.\nIt was unnerving. I had routinely taken that route since moving to my new apartment a year ago, so I should be on auto-pilot, right?"}